				<div class="collapsiblecContent">
					<ul>
						<li>Air elemental<br><br></li>



						<li>Altiniyan al’Azarq<br>
							<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
								<li>An ancient blue dragon</li>
								<li>AKA: the Whispering Death, She of the Storm, The Unseen Ravenger, Storm Bringer</li>


								<li>History
									<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
										<li>Years ago, having gorged herself on the people of the Steppes, she returned to her lair, and like any reptile with a bloated belly, fell into a deep sleep</li>
										<li>A long deep sleep</li>
										<li>A sleep that lasted over 40 years</li>
										<li>So long in fact that the people of the Dry Steppes have assumed she was dead or had moved on</li>
										<li>Few who have seen her have survived, so much of what is spoken of her in hushed tones is rumor</li>
										<li>Many do not believe she ever existed, especially those too young to have witnessed the destruction of her attacks</li>
										<li>Parents tell tales of the Whispering Death to their children to frighten them</li>
									</ol>
								</li>

								<li>Backstory
									<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
										<li>Altiniyan al’Azarq is a very intelligent, calculating and patient creature, willing to observe her prey for hours or even days before making her attack, but when she attacks, she is ruthless and unstoppable</li>
										<li>For meals, she prefers ponies, but will happily snap up any hapless people she encounters</li>
										<li>Her scales are thick, dark blue and crackle with static just before using her deadly breath attack</li>
										<li>The sweet smell of ozone fills the air during and after a recent attack</li>
									</ol>
								</li>

								<li>Attacks
									<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
										<li>Like other ancient dragons, Altiniyan al’Azarq is inherently magical and has learned to use spells and employs it to great effect in her attacks against the helpless people on the Steppes</li>
										<li>Spells
											<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
												<li>Chain Lightning – range: 150’, hit 1 target, then from it, 3 more bolts to any target within 30 of the original targets - 10d8 Lightning, DC 20 DEX save for half damage</li>
												<li>Darkness – range 60’, 15’ radius, duration: 10 minutes, concentration</li>
												<li>Detect Magic</li>
												<li>Dimension Door – 500’ teleport</li>
												<li>Greater Invisibility – duration: 1 minute, concentration</li>
											</ol>
										</li>
										<li>Altiniyan al’Azarq is a calculating creature and does not attack unless she is sure to win</li>
										<li>She usually waits for a natural storm to form (esp. at night), then under the cover of these dark storm clouds, she uses Greater Invisibility to swiftly fly into a community, unleashing her deadly breath attack and attacking with her powerful claws and jaws as she strafes her targets, none of whom can see her, but hear the whoosh of her wings</li>
										<li>After softening up her targets, she will land and begin killing and destroying everything in sight</li>
										<li>Using her Frightful Gaze, most people are helpless as she charges in killing left and right</li>
										<li>When convinced all are dead and/or eaten, she flies away to digest for a week or so before launching another sneak attack</li>
									</ol>
								</li>

								<li>Lair Region
									<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
										<li>The region out to 6 miles around Altiniyan al’Azarq’s lair is pitted with deadly sink holes and thunderstorms rage</li>
										<li>Mindless air elements, often mistaken for large dust devils, regularly wander about</li>
										<li>These conditions tend to drive away (or kill) all but the bravest (or most foolish) of souls</li>
										<li>Locals attribute these phenomena as a place cursed by the gods, calling it “The Cursed” – referring to the storms, the elements and sinkholes alike</li>
									</ol>
								</li>

								<li>Awakened
									<ol start="50" style="margin-left: 30px;">
										<li>However, a party of Paynim recently managed to work their way through these dangers and find the great worm’s lair, a massive cave complex with a huge opening in the ground</li>
										<li>Descending by ropes down into the dark pit, they began exploring the cavern below, ultimately finding the mounds of treasure of the great worm</li>
										<li>Unknown to these explorers, they had managed to awaken Altiniyan al’Azarq with their cries of joy at finding the heaps of wealth</li>
										<li>Though sluggish at first (having been asleep for so long), the dragon observed these intruders as they obliviously cheered at their good fortune</li>
										<li>Suddenly, and without warning, Altiniyan al’Azarq attacked, killing all of the intruders in a matter of moments</li>
										<li>Now awake and hungry after her decades of slumber, the ancient dragon began searching for food</li>
										<li>She has been attacking the people of the Steppes for several weeks now, moving from place to place, preferring to attack at night and during a storm<br><br></li>
									</ol>
								</li>
							</ol>
						</li>


					</ul>
