				<button type="button" class="collapsible1">City of Brass</button>
				<div class="collapsiblecContent">
						<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 30px;">
							<li><%=Maithius%> investigates the fabled <%=City_of_Brass%> at <%=The_Grand_Library_of_Califri%></li>
							<li>Brief history
								<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
									<li>Of the Creation of the Genie
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li>The gods emerge from the void, crafting the elemental planes to forms of their liking</li>
											<li>These planes are filled with formless spirits</li>
											<li><%=Anumon%> created the first genie, <%=Sulymon%> from one of these formless spirit</li>
											<li><%=Sulymon%> is given many tasks, including the creation of other genies</li>
											<li>The genies are the servants of the gods, known as the 1st children, are commanded to begin creating the universe</li>
										</ul>
									</li>

									<li>Of the Crafting of the <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%>
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li><%=Sulymon%> proposes a great city, <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%>, for his people - the gods agree
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>The children of air have no interest in a city, preferring to freedom on the winds</li>
													<li>The children of water have little interest, knowing that all waters will eventually flow to them</li>
													<li>Thus, the children of earth and fire are the primary builders of the great city</li>
												</ul>
											</li>
											<li><%=Sulymon%>'s city is made of gold, silver, gems, jewelry and lapis lazuli</li>
											<li>The city was given to the the genies as thanks, but in accepting, the genies became mortal</li>
											<li>Some of the genies seethed with anger at being made mortal</li>
											<li><%=Sulymon%> placed <%=Iblis%>, the first genie he created, on the throne of <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%></li>
											<li>The city stood for thousands of year, the genies living together in peace</li>
											<li>As <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%> grew, so too did the house of <%=Iblis%> as did their arrogance</li>
											<li>As the creation grew to a close, the house of <%=Iblis%> began to make demands on the <%=Djinn%>, <%=Marid%> and jann</li>
										</ul>
									</li>

									<li>Of the Great Purge and the Exodus of the <%=Djinn%>
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li><%=Iblis%> took many wives from the houses of the genies, siring a host of <%=Efreeti%></li>
											<li>Me also sired many children out of wedlock, causing much animosity among the houses</li>
											<li>When one house threaten to go to <%=Sulymon%> for justice, <%=Iblis%> had the heads of disloyal houses killed</li>
											<li>Those that could, escaped back to their home elemental planes
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>The Emir of <%=Djinn%> and his daughter somehow manage to escape returning to the Elemental Plane of Air, never to return</li>
													<li>The remaining <%=Djinn%> follow their leader and leave the city</li>
													<li>Saddened by the leaving of the <%=Djinn%>, the <%=Marid%> take leave of <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%></li>
												</ul>
											</li>
											<li>The house of <%=Iblis%> now ruled the golden city</li>
										</ul>
									</li>

									<li>Of the Fall of the House of Iblis
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li>The job of creation was nearly complete and the gods set about populating it with the 2nd children (elves, dwarves and humans</li>
											<li><%=Iblis%> was furious that the 2nd children were given the universe, while he and his people were only given a city</li>
											<li>They defied the gods, claiming they deserved more</li>
											<li>The gods were shocked and spoke their harsh judgment against <%=Iblis%> and his followers:
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>Flames burst from their bodies</li>
													<li>Their faces became twisted and horns burst from their once proud brows</li>
												</ul>
											</li>
											<li>The gods then turned to the children of <%=Iblis%>, cursing them:
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>Forever more, there were be enmity and distrust between their house and the 2nd children</li>
													<li>Any mortals killed or enslaved by an <%=Efreet%> would be reborn in paradise</li>
													<li>Any <%=Efreet%> bound to a moral's will would be their slave, passed on from father to son, mother to daughter</li>
												</ul>
											</li>
											<li>The gods again turned to <%=Iblis%>
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>They damned him, granting him rulership in Hell</li>
													<li>The ground opened beneath his feet, casting him into the pit of Hell</li>
												</ul>
											</li>
											<li>The gods cast <%=Mudawwarah_Al_Jin%> to the very edge of the Plane of Fire</li>
											<li>The golden city was instantly turned to brass, its gems and riches charred</li>
										</ul>
									</li>

									<li>The Demise of <%=Sulymon%> the Genie and the Rise of <%=Sulymon%> the Prophet
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li><%=Sulymon%> was shamed by his children's behavior and wept</li>
											<li>Eons passed as he pondered what had gone wrong</li>
											<li>He prayed and begged <%=Anumon%> for guidance, and eventually, his payers were answered in a vision</li>
											<li><%=Sulymon%> wrought great magic to draw the dark from himself eventually defeating his darker half</li>

											<li>Returning to the <%=City_of_Brass%>, <%=Sulymon%> sought to right the many wrongs:
												<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
													<li>He bound the most evil of the <%=Efreet%> into bottles of brass, stoppering them with lead and the seal of <%=Anumon%></li>
													<li>He sent for <%=Cirrishade%>, his daughter, and wed her to <%=Ashur_Ban%>, one of the few <%=Efreet%> who has not sided with <%=Iblis%></li>
													<li>Placing the two upon the Brass Throne, he left the city</li>
													<li>Calling upon <%=Anumon%>'s might, the <%=Plane_of_Molten_Skies%> formed over his princely head, scorched earth and sand</li>
												</ul>
											</li>
										</ul>
									</li>

									<li>Of the <%=City_of_Brass%> and the Coming of the Usurper
										<ul class="circle" style="margin-left: 40px;">
											<li>Many years passed and relative peace reigned again between <%=Djinn%> and <%=Efreet%></li>
											<li>A truce brokered by the marriage of the Sultana and Sultan brought great prosperity to the city</li>
											<li>But not all of the <%=Efreet%> were satisfied - many despised the Sultana and saw <%=Ashur_Ban%> as weak</li>
											<li>Despite their troubles, the love of <%=Ashur_Ban%> and <%=Cirrishade%> grew stronger with each passing year</li>
											<li>Many children were born to them; and to those children, many grandchildren - they were called the <%=Hawanar%></li>
											<li>Unbeknownst to them, a great evil was taking shape within the <%=Eye_of_Fire%></li>
											<li>There in the <%=Eye_of_Fire%> it forged its weapon for the taking of the universe - a brazen scimitar with which to set the very heavens ablaze</li>
											<li>In the <%=Eye_of_Fire%>, the years passed and the creature grew stronger, quietly gathering evil to its side</li>
											<li>Once gathered, the Usurper struck from the <%=Eye_of_Fire%> capturing <%=Efreeti%> fortresses</li>
											<li>Many among them swore it was <%=Iblis%> returned from Hell to lead them once again</li>
											<li>When the Usurper finally arrived at the <%=City_of_Brass%>, he cast down the gates and slew Sultan <%=Ashur_Ban%> in one blow, shattering the resolve of his forces</li>
											<li>At long last, the Usurper claimed the Throne of Brass and has sat there unchallenged ever since</li>
											<li>Claiming the title of Great Sultan, the Usurper freed the evil servants of <%=Iblis%> from their bondage</li>
											<li>He set the <%=Efreet%> to work collecting numerous slaves for the many tasks, and bade them forge weapons of great destructive power to be sold to the highest bidder</li>
										</ul>
									</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
				</div>





